In case you missed it, here are the top sport stories of the
week: 1. SHOCK AS SHANDU HEADS TO BUCS Maritzburg United's versatile Bandile Shandu is set to join Orlando Pirates. 2. CALL TO 'ARREST ACTING PSL CEO' The legal battle between GladAfrica Championship side, Royal AM, and the PSL is getting nasty and seem far from over. 3. SWALLOWS SIGN FORMER PIRATES MIDFIELDER Swallows FC have completed the signing of former Orlando Pirates midfielder Thandani Ntshumayelo on a one-year contract. 4. JUNIOR KHANYE BUYS NEW CAR! The former Kaizer Chiefs dribbling wizard took all and sundry by surprise when he posted himself with his brand new two-door BMW Mini Cooper TwinPower Turbo. 5. JUDGE WHO SENTENCED ZUMA JOINS SAFA Acting Chief Justice Sisi Khampepe, who found former President Jacob Zuma guilty of contempt of court and sentenced him to 15-months direct imprisonment, has found her way to Safa House.